Rating: 3
I made this recipe twice, both times with white sushi rice. I would love to try the brown rice version but have to get my hands on some short-grain brown rice first... The first time there were about 7 of us and this was the only course so I multiplied the recipe by 8, skipped the sprouts and also added sliced plain omelette, but ended up with way too much (perhaps x5 would have been enough). The second time I multiplied by 4, and I was having a potluck at my place and had also made some other food. I expected around 8 people but in the end we were only 4. This time I added salmon row as well as smoked salmon to some of the rolls. I substituted sugar-snap pea sprouts. I also boiled the carrots in both cases because I didn't think that my guests would like raw carrot in their sushi. Anyway, this amount ended up yielding 6 rolls, which were much appreciated at the party. I sent some sushi home with one of my guests and had some leftover that was quickly finished the next day. I learned the second time that for the white rice recipe you are only supposed to add the vinegar mixture after it is cooked (not during). That point was a bit vague. I had made sushi before and this recipe isn't much different (other than the sprouts and the brown rice, which unfortunately I haven't tried), but is just as good as any other sushi I've had.

