Rating: 4
Although I haven't made this exact recipe, I do occasionally make veggie sushi rolls. They do take practice, so don't get discouraged if they turn out looking more like hearts than circles like mine did! Keep in mind, it's like a burrito, but you don't want to over-stuff them. Another helpful tip is to let them "rest" before slicing, but do not refrigerate. The resting allows the moisture to soak in the nori, which is what holds them together. My favorite fillings include avocado, of course, julienned carrots & cucumbers, marinated shiitake mushrooms (I braise them in soy sauce, usually shoyu or tamari, with a little rice wine, then allow them to cool before using them.), and sliced jalapeno, which give them a nice kick. Yum!

