Rating: 3
I've made this several times now, but decided to add my own review now that I emailed the recipe to somebody else! I love this recipe because it uses brown rice, which adds a pleasant hint of nutty flavor (and it's healthier than regular sushi rice.) I suggest the following additional and/or alternative ingredients: green onions, shredded lettuce or baby spinach, alfalfa sprouts, slivers of raw summer squash, marinated, stir-fried extra-firm tofu, cooled and cut into thin strips, lightly steamed asparagus tips (yum!), or pretty much any firm-textured vegetable that can be cut into thin strips and eaten raw or lightly cooked. Also, if you're having trouble finding the equipment - I have a little kit I bought at Barnes & Noble, called Sushi Made Easy - comes with a lovely instruction book, two rolling mats, a rice paddle, and 4 pairs of chopsticks. Handy and helpful.

