Rating: 3
This was my first try with sushi and they turned out nicely. I made white rice because it was in the pantry. I also bought crabmeat and added that to the rolls (so they weren't really vegetarian, oh well). I couldn't find radish sprouts or whatever it was, but used cucumber (the regular kind, not the kind tht was called for) and carrots and avos and crabmeat. They were delish. Took some practice with rolling (and some effort tracking down a bamboo mat and nori sushi wrappers) but once I got going it was smooth sailing. I trippled the recipe because I wanted to take them to a party. I did and they were a HIT. I didn't think this would be a sushi loving crowd but turns out, they vanished. Good - less for me to lug home. Give this recipe a try, even if you're intimidated by it.

